  "title": "Spectrum: $25K reward offered for information on cut fiber optic lines in Spartanburg Co. - NewsBreak",
  "text": "By Isabel Martin ,\n12 hours ago\nSPARTANBURG COUNTY, S.C. (WSPA) — Spectrum has offered a reward after fiber optic lines were “intentionally cut” on Wednesday.\nAccording to the communications company, whoever cut the lines caused a service outage for residents and businesses in Spartanburg County.\nThe incident occurred at the 200 block of Wertz Court in Pacolet, officials shared.\nFiber optic lines cut ‘intentionally’ in Anderson County, deputies say The Spartanburg County Sheriff’s Office confirmed that deputies are assisting in the investigation.\nA company spokesperson said a $25,000 reward is being offered for any information that leads to an arrest.\nKnow something? Contact Spectrum at (833) 404-8477or the sheriff’s office at (864) 503-4500.\nCopyright 2026 Nexstar Media, Inc. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed. For the latest news, weather, sports, and streaming video, head to WSPA 7NEWS.\n1",
